 ('20', '20', 'en_us', 'TV2 KSU', '<p>TV2 is Kent State\'s award-winning television station that strives to be Truly Portage County. From local news and sports to entertainment buzz and important social issues surrounding the region, TV2 covers the Kent State and Portage County area like no other television station can, while educating and preparing students for the future. TV2 is found online with media partner The Kent Stater at kentwired.com, reaching more than 26,000 homes on Spectrum Cable channel 16 and more than 7500 KSU students on campus television station 2-2. </p>', NULL, '', '[]', 'Leisel', 'Kober', 'Student Leader', NULL, '330-672-2584', 'TV2 is the award-winning, student-run television station of Kent State University. TV2 is also Portage County’s only local television station and the best source for local news and original television content. TV2 reaches more than 26,000 homes throughout Portage County on Spectrum (formerly Time Warner Cable) channel 16 and more than 7,500 Kent State students living on-campus on channel 2-2. TV2 is also live streamed on KentWired.com/TV2. With 10 different TV shows, TV2 covers everything from breaking news, local news, weather, sports, entertainment and humor.', NULL, NULL, 'Truly Portage County ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Award-winning television that strives to be \"Truly Portage County\" with news, sports and entertainment programming', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://www.kentwired.com/tv2/', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'centerCenter', '{\"id\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"archived\":0,\"locale\":\"en_us\",\"localeEnabled\":1,\"slug\":null,\"uri\":null,\"dateCreated\":null,\"dateUpdated\":null,\"root\":null,\"lft\":null,\"rgt\":null,\"level\":null,\"searchScore\":null,\"elementId\":0,\"metaType\":\"template\",\"metaPath\":\"\",\"seoMainEntityCategory\":\"CreativeWork\",\"seoMainEntityOfPage\":\"WebPage\",\"seoTitle\":\"TV2 KSU\",\"seoDescription\":\"\",\"seoKeywords\":\"\",\"seoImageTransform\":\"\",\"seoFacebookImageTransform\":\"\",\"seoTwitterImageTransform\":\"\",\"twitterCardType\":\"\",\"openGraphType\":\"\",\"robots\":\"\",\"seoImageId\":null,\"seoTwitterImageId\":null,\"seoFacebookImageId\":null,\"seoTitleUnparsed\":\"\",\"seoDescriptionUnparsed\":\"\",\"seoKeywordsUnparsed\":\"\",\"seoTitleSource\":\"field\",\"seoTitleSourceField\":\"title\",\"seoDescriptionSource\":\"custom\",\"seoDescriptionSourceField\":\"title\",\"seoKeywordsSource\":\"custom\",\"seoKeywordsSourceField\":\"title\",\"seoImageIdSource\":\"custom\",\"seoImageIdSourceField\":\"adBundlePhoto\",\"seoTwitterImageIdSource\":\"custom\",\"seoTwitterImageIdSourceField\":\"adBundlePhoto\",\"seoFacebookImageIdSource\":\"custom\",\"seoFacebookImageIdSourceField\":\"adBundlePhoto\",\"seoCommerceVariants\":null,\"__model__\":\"Craft\\\\Seomatic_MetaFieldModel\"}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, '2017-03-02 19:46:26', '2017-07-23 19:53:44', 'a23b03af-0e18-4a7b-8901-95644568668e'),
 ('21', '21', 'en_us', 'Fusion Magazine', '<p>Fusion is Kent State University\'s LGBTQ magazine. We publish news, entertainment, opinions and interviews for and about the LGBTQ community. Each spring, we release a print issue and we regularly update our website (<a href=\"http://www.thatgaymagazine.com\">www.thatgaymagazine.com</a>) and social media channels year-round. </p>\n<p>Our mission is to promote equality, education and community through journalism. When Fusion was founded, in 2003, marriage equality was not yet legal anywhere in the United States and laws against consensual sex between gay men were overturned that year. LGBTQ rights have significantly advanced since trans women, drag queens and street kids fought back against police violence in 1959. But the community, particularly trans people and people of color, still face substantial adversity. Journalism and storytelling helps humanize the community and its struggle. By publicizing their perspectives and experiences, Fusion helps demonstrate why LGBTQ people need an equal place in society.</p>', NULL, 'meckhous@kent.edu', '[]', 'MJ', 'Eckhouse', 'Student Leader', NULL, '', 'Fusion is Kent State\'s lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender and queer/questioning student advocacy and entertainment magazine. Fusion strives to promote equality and community in northeast Ohio and beyond through journalism and they have been recognized by the Society of Professional Journalists for excellence. Fusion is the only student magazine focusing on LGBTQ issues in the region.', NULL, NULL, 'That Gay Magazine', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Promoting LGBTQ equality and community, through journalism, in northeast Ohio and beyond', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://www.thatgaymagazine.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'centerCenter', '{\"id\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"archived\":0,\"locale\":\"en_us\",\"localeEnabled\":1,\"slug\":null,\"uri\":null,\"dateCreated\":null,\"dateUpdat