 ('22', '22', 'en_us', 'Uhuru', '<p>Uhuru is an award-winning magazine that aims to promote innovation, creativity, and culture through the voice of marginalized students on the Kent State University campus. Having a history of Pan-African teachings and values, Uhuru magazine focuses on the plight of all students around the globe.\n  </p>\n<p>Uhuru, which is Kiswahili for ‘freedom,’ serves as a platform for student creation and expression in art, writing, photography and graphic design, while discussing racial, social and/or political ignorance.\n      </p>', NULL, 'uhurumag1@gmail.com', '[]', 'Sierra', 'Allen', 'Student Leader', NULL, '', 'Uhuru is an award-winning magazine that promotes innovation, creativity and culture through the voice of marginalized students. A derivative of Black Unites Students, Uhuru is focused on the unification of the African-American population but serves as a safe haven for others by reflecting all people of color at Kent State. Uhuru is Kent State\'s only minority news outlet and serves as a platform for student creation and expression in art, writing, photography and graphic design while addressing social issues.', NULL, NULL, 'Voice of the People ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Providing voice for marginalized students at Kent State', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://www.uhurumag.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'centerCenter', '{\"id\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"archived\":0,\"locale\":\"en_us\",\"localeEnabled\":1,\"slug\":null,\"uri\":null,\"dateCreated\":null,\"dateUpdated\":null,\"root\":null,\"lft\":null,\"rgt\":null,\"level\":null,\"searchScore\":null,\"elementId\":0,\"metaType\":\"template\",\"metaPath\":\"\",\"seoMainEntityCategory\":\"CreativeWork\",\"seoMainEntityOfPage\":\"WebPage\",\"seoTitle\":\"Uhuru\",\"seoDescription\":\"\",\"seoKeywords\":\"\",\"seoImageTransform\":\"\",\"seoFacebookImageTransform\":\"\",\"seoTwitterImageTransform\":\"\",\"twitterCardType\":\"\",\"op