 ('498', '161', '21', '235', 'en_us', '13', '', '{\"typeId\":\"21\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Student Media Board \",\"slug\":\"board-members\",\"postDate\":1494414895,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The Student Media Board is a standing University committee. The members of the committee&nbsp;serve \\\"as the institutional publisher or de facto licensee and acts in all matters pertaining to those media that are written or broadcast primarily by students and financed primarily by university-sanctioned student fees.\\\" &nbsp;The SMB reports to the vice president for student affairs and the dean of the College of Communication and Information.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The SMB is primarily responsible for selecting student leaders, approving annual budgets and hearing any grievances that cannot be otherwise resolved. The SMB does not dictate or determine editorial content for Student Media partners and gives responsibility for day-to-day editorial operations to the selected student leaders. The SMB gives day-to-day business operation responsibility to the director of Student Media.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The board is made up of students, staff and faculty across the university, as well as media professionals outside of KSU. Voting members include faculty members appointed by the faculty senate, faculty members appointed by the school of journalism and mass communication faculty advisory committee, the JMC director, the CSI director, USG appointees, a graduate senate appointee, JMC undergraduate students, a JMC graduate student and a media professional. All student leaders, student media advisors and the director of student media serve as non-voting members.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Check out the guidelines, members and meeting minutes below.<br><\\/p>\",\"49\":[\"204\"],\"13\":[\"246\"],\"21\":\"We\'ll go farther together \"}}', '2017-06-05 20:45:26', '2017-06-05 20:45:26', 'a3fba361-0df2-4568-b8c6-f19bdf0b977f'),
 ('499', '58', '9', '235', 'en_us', '30', '', '{\"typeId\":\"9\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"About us\",\"slug\":\"about\",\"postDate\":1492560894,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"55\":\"<p>Advertise with us!<\\/p>\",\"1\":\"<p>We are more than 700 students working with 10 distinct and independent Student Media partners who create unique content distributed across 34 different outlets on multiple platforms. Our students are supported in their efforts by a strong fabric of faculty advisers, professional staff, university support and, of course, financial support from the students of Kent State University.&nbsp;<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Our mission-driven leadership begins here:<\\/strong><strong><em><br><\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong><em>Student Media empowers students<\\/em><\\/strong> through practical, collaborative and professional learning opportunities within an independent, student-led and multi-platform media framework.<strong><em><br><\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong><em>Our students create valued sources<\\/em><\\/strong> of journalism, information, entertainment and advertising and develop meaningful connections with our core audiences.<strong><em><br><\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong><em>We encourage excellence, leadership and accountability<\\/em><\\/strong> as students become innovative, ethical and skilled media producers within a diverse and global society. <br><\\/p>\",\"11\":[\"166\"],\"13\":[\"246\"],\"47\":\"<p>We often have larger ideas than our budget will support. Your generous gift will help our students build on their big ideas. Your gift can be directed at a specific media partner or go to support Student Media in general. &nbsp;<br><\\/p>\",\"21\":\"Through the combined effort of students and faculty, our mission is to provide a professional learning foundation for all.\"}}', '2017-06-05 20:45:42', '2017-06-05 20:45:42', 'ba118ec5-2f3b-4e1a-9601-4ae69b76bf24'),
