 ('659', '161', '21', '1', 'en_us', '15', '', '{\"typeId\":\"21\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Student Media Board \",\"slug\":\"board-members\",\"postDate\":1494414895,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The Student Media Board is a standing University committee. The members of the committee&nbsp;serve \\\"as the institutional publisher or de facto licensee and acts in all matters pertaining to those media that are written or broadcast primarily by students and financed primarily by university-sanctioned student fees.\\\" &nbsp;The SMB reports to the vice president for student affairs and the dean of the College of Communication and Information.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The SMB is primarily responsible for selecting student leaders, approving annual budgets and hearing any grievances that cannot be otherwise resolved. The SMB does not dictate or determine editorial content for Student Media partners and gives responsibility for day-to-day editorial operations to the selected student leaders. The SMB gives day-to-day business operation responsibility to the director of Student Media.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The board is made up of students, staff and faculty across the university, as well as media professionals outside of KSU. Voting members include faculty members appointed by the faculty senate, faculty members appointed by the school of journalism and mass communication faculty advisory committee, the JMC director, the CSI director, USG appointees, a graduate senate appointee, JMC undergraduate students, a JMC graduate student and a media professional. All student leaders, student media advisors and the director of student media serve as non-voting members.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Check out the guidelines, members and meeting minutes below.<br><\\/p>\",\"49\":[\"204\"],\"13\":[\"246\"],\"72\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"link\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"linkName\":\"Policies\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kent.edu\"}}},\"21\":\"We\'ll go farther together \"}}', '2017-06-29 21:04:18', '2017-06-29 21:04:18', '80b2e290-00fe-44a1-a154-80f29b953042'),
 ('660', '161', '21', '1', 'en_us', '16', '', '{\"typeId\":\"21\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Student Media Board \",\"slug\":\"board-members\",\"postDate\":1498770287,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The Student Media Board is a standing University committee. The members of the committee&nbsp;serve \\\"as the institutional publisher or de facto licensee and acts in all matters pertaining to those media that are written or broadcast primarily by students and financed primarily by university-sanctioned student fees.\\\" &nbsp;The SMB reports to the vice president for student affairs and the dean of the College of Communication and Information.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The SMB is primarily responsible for selecting student leaders, approving annual budgets and hearing any grievances that cannot be otherwise resolved. The SMB does not dictate or determine editorial content for Student Media partners and gives responsibility for day-to-day editorial operations to the selected student leaders. The SMB gives day-to-day business operation responsibility to the director of Student Media.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The board is made up of students, staff and faculty across the university, as well as media professionals outside of KSU. Voting members include faculty members appointed by the faculty senate, faculty members appointed by the school of journalism and mass communication faculty advisory committee, the JMC director, the CSI director, USG appointees, a graduate senate appointee, JMC undergraduate students, a JMC graduate student and a media professional. All student leaders, student media advisors and the director of student media serve as non-voting members.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Check out the guidelines, members and meeting minutes below.<br><\\/p>\",\"49\":[\"204\"],\"13\":[\"246\"],\"72\":{\"336\":{\"type\":\"link\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"linkName\":\"University Policy 4-12.1\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kent.edu\"}}},\"21\":\"