 ('662', '58', '9', '1', 'en_us', '40', '', '{\"typeId\":\"9\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"About us\",\"slug\":\"about\",\"postDate\":1492560894,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>For more than 90 years, students at Kent State University have been finding ways to tell stories and disseminate vital and compelling information.\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Even before formal journalism education classes had been established, students were chasing leads and documenting the events shaping our history, sharing their work in the Normal High School News and The Chestnut Burr in 1914, The Kentonian in 1915 and eventually the first issue of The Kent Stater on July 29, 1926.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We now are more than 700 students working with 10 distinct and independent Student Media partners who create unique content distributed across 34 different outlets on multiple platforms. Our students are supported in their efforts by a strong fabric of faculty advisers, professional staff, university support and, of course, financial support from the students of Kent State University.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>And while the methods have varied since those early publications, our core philosophy has remained constant: empower students to create valued sources and encourage excellence.\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Won\\u2019t you join us and continue the story?<\\/p>\\r\\n<hr>\\r\\n<p><strong>Our mission-driven leadership begins here:<\\/strong><strong><em><br><\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>STUDENT MEDIA EMPOWERS STUDENTS<\\/strong> through practical, collaborative and professional learning opportunities within an independent, student-led and multi-platform media framework.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>OUR STUDENTS CREATE <\\/strong>valued sources of journalism, information, entertainment and advertising and develop meaningful connections with our core audiences.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>WE ENCOURAGE EXCELLENCE<\\/strong>, leadership and accountability as students become innovative, ethical and skilled media producers within a diverse and global society. <br><\\/p>\",\"11\":[\"166\"],\"13\":[\"246\"],\"71\":\"Members of the fall 2016 Burr staff pose for a picture. The Burr was recognized as the best student magazine in the country by the Society of Professional Journalists.\",\"70\":[\"311\"],\"47\":\"<p>We like to think big. And sometimes our budget can\'t keep up. Your generous gift helps our students build on their big ideas. Your gift can be directed at a specific media partner or go directly to support Student Media in general. &nbsp;<br><\\/p>\",\"21\":\"Student Media Today.\"}}', '2017-06-29 21:19:20', '2017-06-29 21:19:20', 'cd727fe1-a2f7-4245-b0c3-627eaa391179'),
 ('663', '10', '4', '1', 'en_us', '25', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A Magazine\",\"slug\":\"a-magazine\",\"postDate\":1487886960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>A Magazine is Kent State\'s publication for all things fashion, beauty and culture on campus and beyond. A Magazine focuses on women\'s and men\'s fashion providing its audience with the latest fashion industry news and more in print, online and through social media. It is distributed at Kent State and the Fashion School\\u2019s New York studio.&nbsp;A Magazine steps outside just the Kent State campus. From New York City to Florence, Italy and Hong Kong, back to Kent, Ohio, we have students studying and producing content from all over the world<br><\\/p>\",\"4\":\"amagksu@gmail.com\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"337\"],\"14\":[\"46\"],\"68\":[\"313\"],\"10\":\"\",\"29\":\"A Magazine is Kent State\\u2019s student-run fashion magazine and is the hub for all things fashion, beauty and culture related.\",\"26\":{\"140\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/amagksu\\/\"}},\"141\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/AMagKSU\"}},\"142\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\" http:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/amagksu\\/\"}},\"143\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/theamag.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Fashion. Beauty. Culture. \",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2017-06-30 04:14:10', '2017-06-30 04:14:10', 'ac76098c-f163-4ab1-8ab4-ef4204654e41'),
 ('664', '10', '4', '1', 'en_us', '26', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A Magazine\",\"slug\":\"a-magazine\",\"postDate\":1487886960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>A Magazine is Kent State\'s publication for all things fashion, beauty and culture on campus and beyond. A Magazine focuses on women\'s and men\'s fashion providing its audience with the latest fashion industry news and more in print, online and through social media. It is distributed at Kent State and the Fashion School\\u2019s New York studio.&nbsp;A Magazine steps outside just the Kent State campus. From New York City to Florence, Italy and Hong Kong, back to Kent, Ohio, we have students studying and producing content from all over the world<br><\\/p>\",\"4\":\"amagksu@gmail.com\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"338\"],\"14\":[\"46\"],\"68\":[\"313\"],\"10\":\"\",\"29\":\"A Magazine is Kent State\\u2019s student-run fashion magazine and is the hub for all things fashion, beauty and culture related.\",\"26\":{\"140\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/amagksu\\/\"}},\"141\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/AMagKSU\"}},\"142\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\" http:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/amagksu\\/\"}},\"143\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/theamag.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Fashion. Beauty. Culture. \",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2017-06-30 04:15:07', '2017-06-30 04:15:07', '08ca92b8-05bb-483a-b5df-7e886dc38fc9'),
 ('665', '2', '1', '1', 'en_us', '59', '', '{\"typeId\":\"1\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Kent State Student Media\",\"slug\":\"homepage\",\"postDate\":1495818871,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"61\":[\"58\"],\"55\":\"<p>We have been serving Kent State University and the Kent community for more than 80 years with independent student-produced media. We have the outlets you need to reach the target audience you want.<\\/p>\",\"62\":[\"61\"],\"63\":\"Advertise With Us\",\"1\":\"<p>Kent State Student Media makes the connections you need. Whether you are a student searching for an authentic media experience, a community member wanting to share your story, or simply somebody seeking quality news, information and entertainment, we deliver for you across 34 outlets through print, digital and social media. &nbsp;<br><\\/p>\",\"12\":\"Student Media Connects\",\"13\":[\"240\",\"242\",\"241\",\"244\",\"238\",\"338\"],\"92\":\"<p>We are your direct access to more than 70,000 people. We connect you to our audience through award-winning digital, print, film and broadcast media.<br><\\/p>\",\"93\":[\"59\"],\"64\":\"Our Media Partners\",\"21\":\"Ten media partners.\",\"90\":\"Seven hundred students.\",\"91\":\"One mission.\",\"22\":\"210945217\",\"65\":\"Take a 90-second tour of Kent State Student Media \"}}', '2017-06-30 04:18:40', '2017-06-30 04:18:40', '089c770b-8ef2-4f43-bba0-0ba8773afb2e'),
 ('666', '59', '10', '1', 'en_us', '13', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Media Partners\",\"slug\":\"media-partners-home\",\"postDate\":1489687966,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Ten distinct media partners make up the engine that drives Kent State Student Media forward. Each partner is a unique and independent student organization. They have opted to join together for mutual benefit under the banner of Student Media. At the top of each group is the selected editor, general manager or president who each \\\"have sole authority to determine content for the media they lead and in turn take full responsibility for the content decisions made.\\\" They work with their faculty advisers, and others, to provide professional, high quality content for their audiences. Learn about each media partner below.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"13\":[\"249\"],\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"The engine of Student Media\"}}', '2017-06-30 05:10:23', '2017-06-30 05:10:23', '916a209f-d8d5-42d4-9b68-8f4671fabf73'),
 ('667', '19', '4', '1', 'en_us', '28', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Black Squirrel Radio\",\"slug\":\"black-squirrel-radio\",\"postDate\":1488483960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"42\"],\"1\":\"<p>Black Squirrel Radio is a student-run radio station committed to providing innovative media content inspired by the community of Kent, Ohio, dedicated to professionalism, integrity, creativity and diversity. With 56 different student-hosted shows airing from 10 a.m. to 2 a.m. everyday, we are&nbsp;committed to providing professional industry experience while continuing to be a platform for experimental programming. Through alternative media content, we aim to grow our audience by becoming the destination for students and alumni to remember what was and experience what is college life in Kent, Ohio.<\\/p>\",\"4\":\"general email address goes here\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"299\"],\"14\":[\"47\"],\"68\":[\"236\"],\"10\":\"330-xxx-xxxx\",\"29\":\"BSR is Kent State\\u2019s student-run radio station providing unique and innovative media content online.\",\"26\":{\"156\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/bsrkent\\/\"}},\"157\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\" https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/BSRKent\"}},\"158\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/blacksquirrelradio\\/\"}},\"159\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/blacksquirrelradio.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Kent State\'s Student-Run Radio Station\",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2017-06-30 05:11:04', '2017-06-30 05:11:04', 'a0889dfd-b839-4050-8ac4-9e5dc1f87165'),
 ('668', '19', '4', '1', 'en_us', '29', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Black Squirrel Radio\",\"slug\":\"black-squirrel-radio\",\"postDate\":1488483960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"42\"],\"1\":\"<p>Black Squirrel Radio is a student-run radio station committed to providing innovative media content inspired by the community of Kent, Ohio, dedicated to professionalism, integrity, creativity and diversity. With 56 different student-hosted shows airing from 10 a.m. to 2 a.m. everyday, we are&nbsp;committed to providing professional industry experience while continuing to be a platform for experimental programming. Through alternative media content, we aim to grow our audience by becoming the destination for students and alumni to remember what was and experience what is college life in Kent, Ohio.<\\/p>\",\"4\":\"general email address goes here\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"299\"],\"14\":[\"47\"],\"68\":[\"236\"],\"10\":\"330-xxx-xxxx\",\"29\":\"BSR is Kent State\\u2019s student-run radio station providing unique and innovative media content online.\",\"26\":{\"156\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/bsrkent\\/\"}},\"157\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\" https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/BSRKent\"}},\"158\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/blacksquirrelradio\\/\"}},\"159\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/blacksquirrelradio.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Kent State\'s Student-Run Radio Station\",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2017-06-30 05:11:31', '2017-06-30 05:11:31', 'fd4836f5-ac37-480c-8d4d-cb60a830518f'),
 ('669', '21', '4', '1', 'en_us', '23', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Fusion Magazine\",\"slug\":\"fusion-magazine\",\"postDate\":1488483960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>Fusion is Kent State University\'s LGBTQ magazine. We publish news, entertainment, opinions and interviews for and about the LGBTQ community. Each spring, we release a print issue and we regularly update our website (<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.thatgaymagazine.com\\\">www.thatgaymagazine.com<\\/a>) and social media channels year-round. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our mission is to promote equality, education and community through journalism. When Fusion was founded, in 2003, marriage equality was not yet legal anywhere in the United States and laws against consensual sex between gay men were overturned that year. LGBTQ rights have significantly advanced since trans women, drag queens and street kids fought back against police violence in 1959. But the community, particularly trans people and people of color, still face substantial adversity. Journalism and storytelling helps humanize the community and its struggle. By publicizing their perspectives and experiences, Fusion helps demonstrate why LGBTQ people need an equal place in society.<\\/p>\",\"4\":\"meckhous@kent.edu\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"302\"],\"14\":[\"49\"],\"68\":[\"315\"],\"10\":\"\",\"29\":\"Promoting LGBTQ equality and community, through journalism, in northeast Ohio and beyond.\",\"26\":{\"137\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/ohiofusion\"}},\"138\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/ohiofusion\\/\"}},\"139\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/ohiofusion.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"That Gay Magazine\",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2017-06-30 05:12:12', '2017-06-30 05:12:12', 'cb394fcf-460c-4ed6-8cc2-1617686aee21'),
 ('670', '24', '4', '1', 'en_us', '23', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Luna Negra\",\"slug\":\"luna-negra\",\"postDate\":1488484140,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>Luna Negra, though sometimes under different names, has been around since 1956. It began under the English department, where it found its footing within the campus\\u2019s cultural atmosphere. Since then, the publication has been a staple of the university, witnessing the path Kent State has taken through the decades. We have published works describing the culture of collegiate 1950s, the Kent State shootings, and 9\\/11; the literary pieces published by Luna Negra, written by the students themselves, have chronicled every major cultural and historical event of America. Since its inception, and still to today, Luna Negra is run by students and filled with student content. We strive to foster creative activity across campus and seek to be the keeper and encourager of the student body\\u2019s creative spirit.<\\/p>\",\"4\":\"lunanegramag@gmail.com\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"308\"],\"14\":[\"53\"],\"68\":[\"325\"],\"10\":\"\",\"29\":\"Kent State\\u2019s literary and arts journal publishing a blend of poetry, prose, photography and illustration\",\"26\":{\"129\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/lunanegramag\\/\"}},\"130\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/lunanegramagazine\\/\"}},\"131\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/lunanegramag\"}},\"132\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/www.lunanegramag.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Kent State\'s Literary and Arts Journal\",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2017-06-30 05:12:38', '2017-06-30 05:12:38', '5387c0ab-9fe7-4991-a0da-8fc82e61f5f4'),
 ('671', '60', '11', '1', 'en_us', '22', '', '{\"typeId\":\"11\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Get Involved\",\"slug\":\"get-involved\",\"postDate\":1492711027,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Student Media is open to any students, staff or faculty at Kent State. Start as early as your freshman year and get involved in any of dozens of positions across our 10 Student Media partners. Gain important experience that will set you apart from your fellow students. Come share your voice and gain practical experience to help launch your career. To get started, check out current openings below or contact Kevin Dilley, director of Student Media, at kdilley@kent.edu.<\\/p>\",\"51\":{\"231\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How can I become a student media leader?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Leaders of each Student Media partner are selected by the Student Media Board in the fall and spring of each year for the following semester or semesters. To be considered, you must be must have at least a verified cumulative 2.25 Grade Point Average at the time of application and maintain a cumulative 2.25 GPA and be in good standing with the University during your term as leader. &nbsp;To be a compensated student leader, you must be enrolled in a minimum of eight credit hours as an undergraduate student and a minimum of six as a graduate student during their term. You&nbsp;do not need to be majors enrolled in the School of Journalism and Mass Communication. &nbsp;Candidates applying for leadership positions in the JMC-co-curricular units must have related experience to be considered an applicant.<\\/p>\"}},\"261\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I get paid while working for Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Student Media offers hundreds of paid positions each semester across our 10 Student Media partners. Contact us for more information. <\\/p>\"}},\"262\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I study abroad and still be involved in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Student Media supports students who opt for a semester abroad. Sometimes this can fit into a media outlet\'s content plan for that semester. Also, studying abroad will not affect your ability to continue on a path to a leadership position, if you so choose. <\\/p>\"}},\"263\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Who makes the hiring decisions for Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>It depends on the position you are seeking:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>Top leaders for each media partner are selected by the Student Media Board<\\/li><li>Staff members within each media partner are selected by the student leader in consultation with the adviser<\\/li><li>Staff members in the Student Media office are selected by the professional staff. <\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"264\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How many hours can I work?\",\"answer\":\"<p>That depends on your position and the needs of your outlet. You should talk with your student leader and adviser about the specific needs of each position. If you are in a paid position, you cannot work more than 28 hours each week. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"265\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"If I don\'t see a position I like, can I still work in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Probably, let\'s talk. &nbsp;Student Media is growing and changing as rapidly as the professional fields we strive to emulate. So, if a position doesn\'t exist (and it\'s generally within the wheelhouse of media and communications), let\'s talk and figure out how to make it happen.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"282\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I earn academic credit for my work in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"283\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How long does my employment last once I\'m hired in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"284\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Do I have to reapply for a job in Student Media every semester?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"285\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I work for more than one outlet at the same time during a semester?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"286\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I volunteer at a Student Media publication?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Some jobs are paid, others are volunteer or on a contributor basis. Check with the student leader for each organization to see what opportunities exist at the moment for that media partner.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"287\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Who has editorial control over content?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"288\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Where can I listen to Black Squirrel Radio?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"289\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"On which channel is TV2 broadcast?\",\"answer\":\"\"}}},\"13\":[\"248\"],\"56\":{\"232\":{\"type\":\"employeeOpportunities\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"hiring\":\"A Magazine\",\"position\":\"Graphic Designer\",\"positionDescription\":\"description\",\"contactInformation\":\"Mary Smith\",\"contactEmail\":\"\"}}},\"21\":\"Start your freshman year. Stay until you graduate. \"}}', '2017-06-30 05:13:41', '2017-06-30 05:13:41', '8d9c44fa-4898-4d35-b8c1-33449938931a'),
