dia?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"284\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Do I have to reapply for a job in Student Media every semester?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"285\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I work for more than one outlet at the same time during a semester?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"286\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I volunteer at a Student Media publication?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Some jobs are paid, others are volunteer or on a contributor basis. Check with the student leader for each organization to see what opportunities exist at the moment for that media partner.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"287\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Who has editorial control over content?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"288\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Where can I listen to Black Squirrel Radio?\",\"answer\":\"\"}},\"289\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"On which channel is TV2 broadcast?\",\"answer\":\"\"}}},\"13\":[\"248\"],\"56\":{\"232\":{\"type\":\"employeeOpportunities\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"hiring\":\"A Magazine\",\"position\":\"Graphic Designer\",\"positionDescription\":\"description\",\"contactInformation\":\"Mary Smith\",\"contactEmail\":\"\"}}},\"21\":\"Start your freshman year. Stay until you graduate. \"}}', '2017-06-30 05:13:54', '2017-06-30 05:13:54', 'f9d9d676-dc4b-4a17-9c84-e255f91ecc78'),
 ('673', '58', '9', '235', 'en_us', '41', '', '{\"typeId\":\"9\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"About us\",\"slug\":\"about\",\"postDate\":1492560894,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>For more than 90 years,<\\/strong> students at Kent State University have been finding ways to tell stories and disseminate vital and compelling information.\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Even before formal journalism education classes had been established, students were chasing leads and documenting the events shaping our history, sharing their work in the Normal High School News and The Chestnut Burr in 1914, The Kentonian in 1915 and eventually the first issue of The Kent Stater on July 29, 1926.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>We now are more than 700 students<\\/strong> working with 10 distinct and independent Student Media partners who create unique content distributed across 34 different outlets on multiple platforms. Our students are supported in their efforts by a strong fabric of faculty advisers, professional staff, university support and, of course, financial support from the students of Kent State University.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>And while the methods have varied since those early publications, our core philosophy has remained constant: empower students to create valued sources and encourage excellence.\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Won\\u2019t you join us and continue the story?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<hr>\\r\\n<p><strong>Our mission-driven leadership begins here:<\\/strong><strong><em><br><\\/em><\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>STUDENT MEDIA EMPOWERS STUDENTS<\\/strong> through practical, collaborative and professional learning opportunities within an independent, student-led and multi-platform media framework.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>OUR STUDENTS CREATE <\\/strong>valued sources of journalism, information, entertainment and advertising and develop meaningful connections with our core audiences.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>WE ENCOURAGE EXCELLENCE<\\/strong>, leadership and accountability as students become innovative, ethical and skilled media producers within a diverse and global society. <br><\\/p>\",\"11\":[\"166\"],\"13\":[\"246\"],\"71\":\"Members of the fall 2016 Burr staff pose for a picture. The Burr was recognized as the best student magazine in the country by the Society of Professional Journalists.\",\"70\":[\"311\"],\"47\":\"<p>We like to think big. And sometimes our budget can\'t keep up. Your generous gift helps our students build on their big ideas. Your gift can be directed at a specific media partner or go directly to support Student Media in general. &nbsp;<br><\\/p>\",\"21\":\"Student Media Today.\"}}', '2017-06-30 13:10:25', '2017-06-30 13:10:25', '8c70e6be-f12f-4776-805b-5d6b983583b5'),
 ('674', '101', '4', '235', 'en_us', '25', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"SM Advertising & Marketing \",\"slug\":\"student-media-ad-sales\",\"postDate\":1492116120,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Our Student Media Advertising and Marketing team can help your campus department or local business reach the audience you are seeking. Our staff of account executives will work hand-in-hand to ensure your message is delivered effectively, efficiently and within your budget. Kent State Student Media has 10 different media partners and more than 30 outlets to reach your target market. We provide advertising, promotional item design and ordering, design services, video and audio production, and mobile DJ services. Contact our team today to get started.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"4\":\"ads@ksustudentmedia.com\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"304\"],\"14\":[\"312\"],\"68\":[\"318\"],\"10\":\"330-672-6303\",\"29\":\"An innovative, energetic team connecting our clients to our media partners and signature brands such as KentWired, KentCribs and Transitions\",\"26\":\"\",\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"A multi-service, multim-platform solution\",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2017-06-30 13:21:57', '2017-06-30 13:21:57', '0202e9ea-aca6-4a9e-b97c-9c54b6d17400'),
 ('675', '165', '8', '235', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"8\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Lorie Bednar\",\"slug\":\"lorie-bednar\",\"postDate\":1493055420,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Lorie Bednar joined Kent State\\u2019s School of Journalism and Mass Communication in 2015 as an administrative clerk in the Kent State Student Media office. She now shares her time between both offices. (Other information you want to add)<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Words to Live By:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Be Where Your Feet Are \\u2013 Anonymous<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Personal<\\/strong>:<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Lorie is a graduate of Kent State University and loves everything about her Alma mater. If you don\\u2019t find her on campus, chances are you may run into her downtown and throughout Kent, where she lives and enjoys spending time with her husband and three kids. Two of her greatest achievements are winning an Associated Press award for enterprise writing and being the illustrator of a book jacket.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>I can help you with:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li><p>KEYS!<\\/p><\\/li><li><p>Staff lists<\\/p><\\/li><li><p>Job offers<\\/p><\\/li><li><p>Travel<\\/p><\\/li><li>General questions<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"4\":\"\",\"5\":[\"officeStaff\"],\"6\":\"Lorie\",\"19\":\"\",\"8\":\"Office Manager\\/Miracle Worker\",\"7\":\"Bednar\",\"10\":\"330-672-3290\"}}', '2017-06-30 13:28:32', '2017-06-30 13:28:32', '5fdcec37-5190-4cdb-a0f1-9c18de01fe22'),
 ('676', '165', '8', '235', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"8\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Lorie Bednar\",\"slug\":\"lorie-bednar\",\"postDate\":1493055420,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Lorie Bednar joined Kent State\\u2019s School of Journalism and Mass Communication in 2015 as an administrative clerk in the Kent State Student Media office. She now shares her time between both offices. (Other information you want to add)<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Words to Live By:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Be Where Your Feet Are \\u2013 Anonymous<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Personal<\\/strong>:<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Lorie is a graduate of Kent State University and loves everything about her Alma mater. If you don\\u2019t find her on campus, chances are you may run into her downtown and throughout Kent, where she lives and enjoys spending time with her husband and three kids. Two of her greatest achievements are winning an Associated Press award for enterprise writing and being the illustrator of a book jacket.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>I can help you with:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li><p>KEYS!<\\/p><\\/li><li><p>Staff lists<\\/p><\\/li><li><p>Job offers<\\/p><\\/li><li><p>Travel<\\/p><\\/li><li>General questions<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"4\":\"lbednar@kent.edu\",\"5\":[\"officeStaff\"],\"6\":\"Lorie\",\"19\":\"\",\"8\":\"Office Manager\\/Miracle Worker\",\"7\":\"Bednar\",\"10\":\"330-672-3290\"}}', '2017-06-30 13:30:47', '2017-06-30 13:30:47', '61bacf12-999a-4519-a0ce-fb98ec0c9d3a'),
 ('677', '45', '8', '235', 'en_us', '9', '', '{\"typeId\":\"8\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kevin Dilley\",\"slug\":\"kevin-dilley\",\"postDate\":1489335420,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Kevin serves Student Media by providing management of our business and advising operations. He also works with student leaders, the board, faculty and other key partners to set a strategic direction for Student Media and mentors and advises student leaders. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Words to Live By:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>If you want to go fast, go alone. If you want to go far, go together. &nbsp;~ origin unknown.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Personal:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>I\\u2019ve traveled to Siberia, Malaysia, Mexico and 46 of 50 states in the U.S. I love going places and meeting new people, but I always yearn to return home. For me, that\\u2019s in Hudson with my two children, mi media naranja (si, hablo espa\\u00f1ol), and Pancho, my very best friend because, well he\\u2019s a dog and I\\u2019m a man. I hold degrees in journalism and visual communication from the University of Missouri and Ohio University. I\\u2019ve worked as a reporter, writer, photojournalist, editor, designer, web designer, project manager, consultant, professor and adviser. I love what I do because I\\u2019m constantly inspired by my students who bring ideas, enthusiasm, opportunity and optimism to this place every day.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>I can help you with:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li><p>General questions<\\/p><\\/li><li><p>Strategic planning<\\/p><\\/li><li><p>Idea development<\\/p><\\/li><li><p>Budgets<\\/p><\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"4\":\"kdilley@kent.edu\",\"5\":[\"director\",\"nonVoting\",\"officeStaff\"],\"6\":\"Kevin \",\"19\":[\"292\"],\"8\":\"Director of Student Media\",\"7\":\"Dilley\",\"10\":\"330-672-0887\"}}', '2017-06-30 13:32:18', '2017-06-30 13:32:18', 'fc13f5d0-89a3-45f1-bbfd-5bf3f2ad95f0'),
