 ('685', '161', '21', '235', 'en_us', '18', '', '{\"typeId\":\"21\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Student Media Board \",\"slug\":\"board-members\",\"postDate\":1498770287,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>As a standing University committee<\\/strong>, the Student Media Board serves \\\"as the institutional publisher or de facto licensee and acts in all matters pertaining to those media that are written or broadcast primarily by students and financed primarily by university-sanctioned student fees.\\\" &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>The SMB is primarily responsible for selecting student leaders, approving annual budgets and hearing any grievances that cannot be otherwise resolved. <\\/strong>The SMB does not dictate or determine editorial content for Student Media partners and gives responsibility for day-to-day editorial operations to the selected student leaders. Responsibility for short term business operations and long-term strategy is delegated to the director of Student Media.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>The board is made up of students, staff and faculty across the university, as well as media professionals outside of KSU. Including:<\\/strong><\\/p><p>&nbsp;\\u2022&nbsp;Faculty members appointed by the faculty senate<\\/p><p>\\u2022 Faculty members appointed by the School of Journalism and Mass Communication faculty advisory committee<\\/p><ul><li>Director of Journalism and Mass Communication<\\/li><li>Director of the Center for Student Involvement<\\/li><li>Students appointed by the Undergraduate Student Government<\\/li><li>A graduate senate student appointee<\\/li><li>JMC undergraduate students<\\/li><li>JMC graduate student&nbsp;<\\/li><li>A media professional.&nbsp;<\\/li><li>All student leaders, student media advisers and the director of student media serve as non-voting members.&nbsp;<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Check out the guidelines, members and meeting minutes below.<br><\\/p>\",\"49\":[\"204\"],\"13\":[\"246\"],\"72\":{\"336\":{\"type\":\"link\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"linkName\":\"University Policy 4-12.1\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.kent.edu\\/policyreg\\/administrative-policy-regarding-student-media-policy-board\"}}},\"21\":\"We\'ll go farther together \"}}', '2017-06-30 14:34:50', '2017-06-30 14:34:50', '65bf6043-aa0c-4625-8c1b-1a740908f4be'),
 ('686', '161', '21', '235', 'en_us', '19', '', '{\"typeId\":\"21\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Student Media Board \",\"slug\":\"board-members\",\"postDate\":1498770287,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>As a standing University committee<\\/strong>, the Student Media Board serves \\\"as the institutional publisher or de facto licensee and acts in all matters pertaining to those media that are written or broadcast primarily by students and financed primarily by university-sanctioned student fees.\\\" &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>The SMB is primarily responsible for selecting student leaders, approving annual budgets and hearing any grievances that cannot be otherwise resolved. <\\/strong>The SMB does not dictate or determine editorial content for Student Media partners and gives responsibility for day-to-day editorial operations to the selected student leaders. Responsibility for short term business operations and long-term strategy is delegated to the director of Student Media.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>The board is made up of students, staff and faculty across the university, as well as media professionals outside of KSU. These include:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>&nbsp;Faculty members appointed by the faculty senate<\\/li><li>Faculty members appointed by the School of Journalism and Mass Communication faculty advisory committee<\\/li><li>Director of Journalism and Mass Communication<\\/li><li>Director of the Center for Student Involvement<\\/li><li>Students appointed by the Undergraduate Student Government<\\/li><li>A graduate senate student appointee<\\/li><li>JMC undergraduate students<\\/li><li>JMC graduate student&nbsp;<\\/li><li>A media professional<\\/li><li>All selected Student Media leaders, advisers and the director of Student Media serve as non-voting members.&nbsp;<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Check out the guidelines, members and meeting minutes below.<br><\\/p>\",\"49\":[\"204\"],\"13\":[\"246\"],\"72\":{\"336\":{\"type\":\"link\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"linkName\":\"University Policy 4-12.1\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.kent.edu\\/policyreg\\/administrative-policy-regarding-student-media-policy-board\"}}},\"21\":\"We\'ll go farther together \"}}', '2017-06-30 14:37:04', '2017-06-30 14:37:04', '53f8092c-393e-4de6-b1fe-b8034ac27971'),
 ('687', '21', '4', '235', 'en_us', '24', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Fusion Magazine\",\"slug\":\"fusion-magazine\",\"postDate\":1488483960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>Fusion is Kent State University\'s LGBTQ magazine. We publish news, entertainment, opinions and interviews for and about the LGBTQ community. Each spring, we release a print issue and we regularly update our website (<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.thatgaymagazine.com\\\">www.thatgaymagazine.com<\\/a>) and social media channels year-round. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our mission is to promote equality, education and community through journalism. When Fusion was founded, in 2003, marriage equality was not yet legal anywhere in the United States and laws against consensual sex between gay men were overturned that year. LGBTQ rights have significantly advanced since trans women, drag queens and street kids fought back against police violence in 1959. But the community, particularly trans people and people of color, still face substantial adversity. Journalism and storytelling helps humanize the community and its struggle. By publicizing their perspectives and experiences, Fusion helps demonstrate why LGBTQ people need an equal place in society.<\\/p>\",\"4\":\"meckhous@kent.edu\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"302\"],\"14\":[\"49\"],\"68\":[\"315\"],\"10\":\"\",\"29\":\"Promoting LGBTQ equality and community, through journalism, in northeast Ohio and beyond.\",\"26\":{\"137\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/ohiofusion\"}},\"138\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/ohiofusion\\/\"}},\"139\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/ohiofusion.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"That Gay Magazine\",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.thatgaymagazine.com\"}}', '2017-06-30 14:41:19', '2017-06-30 14:41:19', 'bef6d51f-8c4a-4bb0-9ee7-bada2d8d6ee4'),
