 ('723', '161', '21', '267', 'en_us', '20', '', '{\"typeId\":\"21\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Student Media Board \",\"slug\":\"board-members\",\"postDate\":1498770287,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>As a standing University committee<\\/strong>, the Student Media Board serves \\\"as the institutional publisher or de facto licensee and acts in all matters pertaining to those media that are written or broadcast primarily by students and financed primarily by university-sanctioned student fees.\\\" &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>The SMB is primarily responsible for selecting student leaders, approving annual budgets and hearing any grievances that cannot be otherwise resolved. <\\/strong>The SMB does not dictate or determine editorial content for Student Media partners and gives responsibility for day-to-day editorial operations to the selected student leaders. Responsibility for short term business operations and long-term strategy is delegated to the director of Student Media.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>The board is made up of students, staff and faculty across the university, as well as media professionals outside of KSU. These include:<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>Faculty members appointed by the faculty senate<\\/li><li>Faculty members appointed by the School of Journalism and Mass Communication faculty advisory committee<\\/li><li>Director of Journalism and Mass Communication<\\/li><li>Director of the Center for Student Involvement<\\/li><li>Students appointed by the Undergraduate Student Government<\\/li><li>A graduate senate student appointee<\\/li><li>JMC undergraduate students<\\/li><li>JMC graduate student&nbsp;<\\/li><li>A media professional<\\/li><li>All selected Student Media leaders, advisers and the director of Student Media serve as non-voting members.&nbsp;<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Check out the guidelines, members and meeting minutes below.<br><\\/p>\",\"49\":[\"204\"],\"13\":[\"246\"],\"72\":{\"336\":{\"type\":\"link\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"linkName\":\"University Policy 4-12.1\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.kent.edu\\/policyreg\\/administrative-policy-regarding-student-media-policy-board\"}}},\"21\":\"We\'ll go farther together \"}}', '2017-07-05 13:52:12', '2017-07-05 13:52:12', '34eb7555-e070-4491-96f9-fdf1d6a6a159'),
 ('724', '166', '22', '267', 'en_us', '22', '', '{\"typeId\":\"22\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Support Us\",\"slug\":\"support-us\",\"postDate\":1493318469,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>We like to think big. And sometimes our budget can\'t keep up. Your generous gift helps our students build on their big ideas. Your gift can be directed at a specific media partner or go directly to support Student Media in general. Past support has helped us send students to cover election night 2016 in New York City, send other students to California to cover the NCAA basketball tournament, and has helped other students produce full-length feature films. No gift is too small. We\'ll put 100% of your donation to work immediately.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"77\":{\"349\":{\"type\":\"fundraiserInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"fundraiserTitle\":\"Test Fundraiser\",\"description\":\"<p>This is just a test to see how this displays as the second fundraiser. <\\/p>\",\"linkName\":\"Test link to support us\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www.cnn.com\"}},\"334\":{\"type\":\"fundraiserInfo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"fundraiserTitle\":\"General fundraiser\",\"description\":\"<p>Go here anytime to support your favorite media partner or Student Media in general. <\\/p>\",\"linkName\":\"Support Us\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/secure2.convio.net\\/ksu\\/site\\/SPageNavigator\\/Student_media_designated_giving_form.html#\\/\"}}},\"13\":[\"248\"],\"21\":\"We\'ll go farther together\"}}', '2017-07-05 14:00:15', '2017-07-05 14:00:15', '6638d665-66b7-42d1-a9d9-2d603849a888'),
 ('725', '60', '11', '235', 'en_us', '24', '', '{\"typeId\":\"11\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Get Involved\",\"slug\":\"get-involved\",\"postDate\":1492711027,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Student Media is open to any students, staff or faculty at Kent State. Start as early as your freshman year and get involved in any of dozens of positions across our 10 Student Media partners. Gain important experience that will set you apart from your fellow students. Come share your voice and gain practical experience to help launch your career. To get started, check out current openings below or contact Kevin Dilley, director of Student Media, at kdilley@kent.edu.<\\/p>\",\"51\":{\"231\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How can I become a student media leader?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Leaders of each Student Media partner are selected by the Student Media Board in the fall and spring of each year for the following semester or semesters. To be considered, you must be must have at least a verified cumulative 2.25 Grade Point Average at the time of application and maintain a cumulative 2.25 GPA and be in good standing with the University during your term as leader. &nbsp;To be a compensated student leader, you must be enrolled in a minimum of eight credit hours as an undergraduate student and a minimum of six as a graduate student during their term. You&nbsp;do not need to be majors enrolled in the School of Journalism and Mass Communication. &nbsp;Candidates applying for leadership positions in the JMC-co-curricular units must have related experience to be considered an applicant.<\\/p>\"}},\"261\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I get paid while working for Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Student Media offers hundreds of paid positions each semester across our 10 Student Media partners. Contact us for more information. <\\/p>\"}},\"262\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I study abroad and still be involved in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Student Media supports students who opt for a semester abroad. Sometimes this can fit into a media outlet\'s content plan for that semester. Also, studying abroad will not affect your ability to continue on a path to a leadership position, if you so choose. <\\/p>\"}},\"263\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Who makes the hiring decisions for Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>It depends on the position you are seeking:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>Top leaders for each media partner are selected by the Student Media Board<\\/li><li>Staff members within each media partner are selected by the student leader in consultation with the adviser<\\/li><li>Staff members in the Student Media office are selected by the professional staff. <\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"264\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How many hours can I work?\",\"answer\":\"<p>That depends on your position and the needs of your outlet. You should talk with your student leader and adviser about the specific needs of each position. If you are in a paid position, you cannot work more than 28 hours each week. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"265\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"If I don\'t see a position I like, can I still work in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Probably, let\'s talk. &nbsp;Student Media is growing and changing as rapidly as the professional fields we strive to emulate. So, if a position doesn\'t exist (and it\'s generally within the wheelhouse of media and communications), let\'s talk and figure out how to make it happen.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"282\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I earn academic credit for my work in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Consult with your academic adviser to see if this is allowed through your program. Some schools allow this and others don\'t. &nbsp;Student Media cooperates with the various academic units on campus.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"283\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How long does my employment last once I\'m hired in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Employment length varies from individual to individual and is decided by the the media partner student leader. &nbsp;Most last until the end of the semester, but other arrangements are possible. &nbsp;Please talk with the student leader for the media partner with which you work or for which you are interested in working. Student leaders have the responsibility to remove staff members who are not performing well and\\/or are not following rules and regulations of Student Media. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"284\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Do I have to reapply for a job in Student Media every semester?\",\"answer\":\"<p>This depends on your job and the media parter for which you work. &nbsp;If your work for a media partner where a new editor is elected each semester, you\'ll likely have to reapply. &nbsp;Some partners have student leaders elected for an entire academic year. It\'s possible that this leader will hire positions for the whole year. This is their decision. <\\/p>\"}},\"285\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I work for more than one outlet at the same time during a semester?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. The university limits your paid hours to 28 hours per week in total for all university jobs for which you are paid. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"286\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I volunteer at a Student Media publication?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Some jobs are paid, others are volunteer or on a contributor basis. Check with the student leader for each organization to see what opportunities exist at the moment for that media partner.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"287\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Who has editorial control over content?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Student editors and student managers have sole authority to determine content for the media they lead and in turn take full responsibility for the content decisions made.<\\/p>\"}},\"288\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Where can I listen to Black Squirrel Radio?\",\"answer\":\"<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/blacksquirrelradio.com\\\">http:\\/\\/blacksquirrelradio.com<\\/a><\\/p>\"}},\"289\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"On which channel is TV2 broadcast?\",\"answer\":\"<p>We broadcast on channel 2.2 on Kent State\'s campus, and off-campus on Charter Spectrum channel 16. &nbsp;TV2 also streams live and archives shows at www.kentwired.com\\/tv2.<\\/p>\"}}},\"13\":[\"248\"],\"56\":{\"232\":{\"type\":\"employeeOpportunities\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"hiring\":\"A Magazine\",\"position\":\"Graphic Designer\",\"positionDescription\":\"description\",\"contactInformation\":\"Mary Smith\",\"contactEmail\":\"\"}}},\"21\":\"Start your freshman year. Stay until you graduate. \"}}', '2017-07-05 14:11:51', '2017-07-05 14:11:51', 'ac560928-6f36-4ba9-ab77-ef59ebdcdb0e'),
 ('726', '329', '4', '235', 'en_us', '11', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kent Cribs\",\"slug\":\"kent-cribs\",\"postDate\":1498766820,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"69\"],\"1\":\"<p>The premier apartment finder for Kent, Ohio and Kent State University. &nbsp;If you\'re looking for a place to live, you\'ll find ads with full-color photos, floor plans, videos and direct contact to property owners. If you\'re looking to reach students, staff, faculty and community members, this is your place. We get visitors from all over Ohio and the world looking for the perfect place to call home for four years or more.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"4\":\"ads@ksustudentmedia.com\",\"36\":\"\",\"13\":[\"343\"],\"14\":[\"331\"],\"68\":[\"330\"],\"10\":\"330-672-2586\",\"29\":\"Kent\'s premier apartment-finding website\",\"26\":{\"342\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"www.kentcribs.com\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Your apartment search just got easier\",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kentcribs.com\"}}', '2017-07-05 14:41:59', '2017-07-05 14:41:59', 'fdacf255-998a-4b10-b5e0-e79a490f97aa'),
 ('727', '101', '4', '235', 'en_us', '28', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"SM Advertising & Marketing \",\"slug\":\"student-media-ad-sales\",\"postDate\":1492116120,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":\"\",\"1\":\"<p>Our Student Media Advertising and Marketing team can help your campus department or local business reach the audience you are seeking. Our staff of account executives will work hand-in-hand to ensure your message is delivered effectively, efficiently and within your budget. Kent State Student Media has 10 different media partners and more than 30 outlets to reach your target market. We provide advertising, promotional item design and ordering, design services, video and audio production, and mobile DJ services. Contact our team today to get started.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"4\":\"ads@ksustudentmedia.com\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"304\"],\"14\":[\"312\"],\"68\":[\"318\"],\"10\":\"330-672-6303\",\"29\":\"An innovative, energetic team connecting our clients to our media partners and signature brands such as KentWired, KentCribs and Transitions\",\"26\":\"\",\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Multi-service, multi-platform solutions\",\"89\":\"https:\\/\\/kentstatestudentmedia.com\\/advertising\"}}', '2017-07-05 14:42:15', '2017-07-05 14:42:15', 'c7508c39-c0b8-40c1-b83e-1e562737f4cf'),
 ('728', '10', '4', '235', 'en_us', '29', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A Magazine\",\"slug\":\"a-magazine\",\"postDate\":1487886960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>A Magazine is Kent State\'s publication for all things fashion, beauty and culture on campus and beyond. A Magazine focuses on women\'s and men\'s fashion providing its audience with the latest fashion industry news and more in print, online and through social media. It is distributed at Kent State and the Fashion School\\u2019s New York studio.&nbsp;A Magazine steps outside just the Kent State campus. From New York City to Florence, Italy and Hong Kong, back to Kent, Ohio, we have students studying and producing content from all over the world<br><\\/p>\",\"4\":\"amagksu@gmail.com\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"338\"],\"14\":[\"46\"],\"68\":[\"313\"],\"10\":\"\",\"29\":\"A Magazine is Kent State\\u2019s student-run fashion magazine and is the hub for all things fashion, beauty and culture related\",\"26\":{\"140\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/amagksu\\/\"}},\"141\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/AMagKSU\"}},\"142\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\" http:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/amagksu\\/\"}},\"143\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/theamag.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Fashion. Beauty. Culture. \",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.theamag.com\"}}', '2017-07-05 14:42:40', '2017-07-05 14:42:40', '58b9a1ce-fc42-4100-8780-251b8c0f2385'),
 ('729', '21', '4', '235', 'en_us', '25', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Fusion Magazine\",\"slug\":\"fusion-magazine\",\"postDate\":1488483960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>Fusion is Kent State University\'s LGBTQ magazine. We publish news, entertainment, opinions and interviews for and about the LGBTQ community. Each spring, we release a print issue and we regularly update our website (<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.thatgaymagazine.com\\\">www.thatgaymagazine.com<\\/a>) and social media channels year-round. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our mission is to promote equality, education and community through journalism. When Fusion was founded, in 2003, marriage equality was not yet legal anywhere in the United States and laws against consensual sex between gay men were overturned that year. LGBTQ rights have significantly advanced since trans women, drag queens and street kids fought back against police violence in 1959. But the community, particularly trans people and people of color, still face substantial adversity. Journalism and storytelling helps humanize the community and its struggle. By publicizing their perspectives and experiences, Fusion helps demonstrate why LGBTQ people need an equal place in society.<\\/p>\",\"4\":\"meckhous@kent.edu\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"302\"],\"14\":[\"49\"],\"68\":[\"315\"],\"10\":\"\",\"29\":\"Promoting LGBTQ equality and community, through journalism, in northeast Ohio and beyond\",\"26\":{\"137\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/ohiofusion\"}},\"138\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/ohiofusion\\/\"}},\"139\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/ohiofusion.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"That Gay Magazine\",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.thatgaymagazine.com\"}}', '2017-07-05 14:42:50', '2017-07-05 14:42:50', '97f566bc-b1ad-4c6e-b151-26ac852290e4'),
