 ('834', '59', '10', '1', 'en_us', '14', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Media Partners\",\"slug\":\"media-partners-home\",\"postDate\":1489687966,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Ten distinct media partners make up the engine that drives Kent State Student Media forward. Each partner is a unique and independent student organization. They have opted to join together for mutual benefit under the banner of Student Media. At the top of each group is the selected editor, general manager or president who each \\\"have sole authority to determine content for the media they lead and in turn take full responsibility for the content decisions made.\\\" They work with their faculty advisers, and others, to provide professional, high quality content for their audiences. Learn about each media partner below.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"13\":[\"249\"],\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"The engine of Student Media\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:35:46', '2017-07-17 20:35:46', 'a87d1658-71c9-4875-8506-d397e5b38710'),
 ('835', '19', '4', '1', 'en_us', '33', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Black Squirrel Radio\",\"slug\":\"black-squirrel-radio\",\"postDate\":1488483960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"42\"],\"1\":\"<p>Black Squirrel Radio is a student-run radio station committed to providing innovative media content inspired by the community of Kent, Ohio, dedicated to professionalism, integrity, creativity and diversity. With 56 different student-hosted shows airing from 10 a.m. to 2 a.m. everyday, we are&nbsp;committed to providing professional industry experience while continuing to be a platform for experimental programming. Through alternative media content, we aim to grow our audience by becoming the destination for students and alumni to remember what was and experience what is college life in Kent, Ohio.<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"299\"],\"14\":[\"47\"],\"68\":[\"236\"],\"29\":\"BSR is Kent State\\u2019s student-run radio station providing unique and innovative media content online.\",\"26\":{\"156\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/bsrkent\\/\"}},\"157\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\" https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/BSRKent\"}},\"158\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/blacksquirrelradio\\/\"}},\"159\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/blacksquirrelradio.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":{\"340\":{\"type\":\"link\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"linkName\":\"Listen Live\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/blacksquirrelradio.com\"}}},\"21\":\"Kent State\'s Student-Run Radio Station\",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.blacksquirrelradio.com\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:36:55', '2017-07-17 20:36:55', '5bb7451d-1c05-4b53-8d95-6e283cc2e566'),
 ('836', '21', '4', '1', 'en_us', '27', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Fusion Magazine\",\"slug\":\"fusion-magazine\",\"postDate\":1488483960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>Fusion is Kent State University\'s LGBTQ magazine. We publish news, entertainment, opinions and interviews for and about the LGBTQ community. Each spring, we release a print issue and we regularly update our website (<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.thatgaymagazine.com\\\">www.thatgaymagazine.com<\\/a>) and social media channels year-round. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our mission is to promote equality, education and community through journalism. When Fusion was founded, in 2003, marriage equality was not yet legal anywhere in the United States and laws against consensual sex between gay men were overturned that year. LGBTQ rights have significantly advanced since trans women, drag queens and street kids fought back against police violence in 1959. But the community, particularly trans people and people of color, still face substantial adversity. Journalism and storytelling helps humanize the community and its struggle. By publicizing their perspectives and experiences, Fusion helps demonstrate why LGBTQ people need an equal place in society.<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"302\"],\"14\":[\"49\"],\"68\":[\"315\"],\"29\":\"Promoting LGBTQ equality and community, through journalism, in northeast Ohio and beyond\",\"26\":{\"137\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/ohiofusion\"}},\"138\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/ohiofusion\\/\"}},\"139\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/ohiofusion.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":{\"374\":{\"type\":\"link\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"linkName\":\"Shop for Fusion merchandise\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/commerce.cashnet.com\\/fusion\"}},\"375\":{\"type\":\"link\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"linkName\":\"Donate to Fusion\",\"linkUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/secure2.convio.net\\/ksu\\/site\\/Donation2;jsessionid=00000000.app267a?df_id=3801&mfc_pref=T&3801.donation=form1&NONCE_TOKEN=25CA3E954A9AB4B707A852A62582933E\"}}},\"21\":\"That Gay Magazine\",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.thatgaymagazine.com\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:37:24', '2017-07-17 20:37:24', '2b7a9dd3-84f2-44c0-ae39-79c6f5cd7502'),
 ('837', '25', '4', '1', 'en_us', '34', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"KSU Independent Films\",\"slug\":\"ksu-independent-films\",\"postDate\":1488484140,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"42\"],\"1\":\"<p>Kent State University Independent Films takes students who have a passion for film, and gives them the opportunity for real experience. KSUIF works as a student-run production company, where we produce a wide variety of content including webseries, short films, award-winning music videos, documentaries, TV shows, and, most important, feature length films.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"238\"],\"14\":[\"370\"],\"68\":[\"328\"],\"29\":\"KSUIF is a production company that teaches, inspires and prepares filmmakers for the real-world industry \",\"26\":{\"37\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/www.twitter.com\\/ksuif\"}},\"225\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/ksuindependentfilms\\/\"}},\"226\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/kentstatefilms.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Making movies and more \",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/kentstatefilms.com\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:38:07', '2017-07-17 20:38:07', '20ecb556-1c58-414b-902c-0958b9572086'),
 ('838', '101', '4', '1', 'en_us', '33', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"SM Advertising & Marketing \",\"slug\":\"student-media-ad-sales\",\"postDate\":1492116120,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"368\"],\"1\":\"<p>Our Student Media Advertising and Marketing team can help your campus department or local business reach the audience you are seeking. Our staff of account executives will work hand-in-hand to ensure your message is delivered effectively, efficiently and within your budget. Kent State Student Media has 10 different media partners and more than 30 outlets to reach your target market. We provide advertising, promotional item design and ordering, design services, video and audio production, and mobile DJ services. Contact our team today to get started.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"304\"],\"14\":[\"364\"],\"68\":[\"318\"],\"29\":\"An innovative, energetic team connecting our clients to our media partners and signature brands such as KentWired, KentCribs and Transitions\",\"26\":\"\",\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Multi-service, multi-platform solutions\",\"89\":\"https:\\/\\/kentstatestudentmedia.com\\/advertising\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:38:29', '2017-07-17 20:38:29', '21b05dc9-2e58-4475-8065-c63e8db3101f'),
 ('839', '22', '4', '1', 'en_us', '23', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Uhuru\",\"slug\":\"uhuru\",\"postDate\":1488483960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>Uhuru is an award-winning magazine that aims to promote innovation, creativity, and culture through the voice of marginalized students on the Kent State University campus. Having a history of Pan-African teachings and values, Uhuru magazine focuses on the plight of all students around the globe.\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Uhuru, which is Kiswahili for \\u2018freedom,\\u2019 serves as a platform for student creation and expression in art, writing, photography&nbsp;and graphic design, while discussing racial, social and\\/or political ignorance.\\r\\n      <\\/p>\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"270\"],\"14\":[\"56\"],\"68\":[\"320\"],\"29\":\"Providing voice for marginalized students at Kent State\",\"26\":{\"133\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/uhurumag\\/\"}},\"134\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/UhuruMag\"}},\"135\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/uhurumagazine\\/\"}},\"136\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"Uhurumag.com\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Voice of the People \",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.uhurumag.com\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:38:54', '2017-07-17 20:38:54', '31aaf605-ee3f-4477-8c63-3c1fac6df8ac'),
 ('840', '23', '4', '1', 'en_us', '27', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"KentWired\",\"slug\":\"kentwired\",\"postDate\":1488484080,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"69\"],\"1\":\"<p>KentWired.com is the shared website for two Student Media partners, The Kent Stater and TV2 KSU. The site features top news, entertainment, community and campus news, sports and video. KentWired is the place to turn to for everything Kent and Portage County. The site also features classifieds, TV2 newscasts and entertainment shows and a live stream to TV2. KentWired is a key source for news during the summer. With 40,000 unique visitors per month, KentWired is a top news source in Kent and Portage County.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"\",\"13\":[\"272\"],\"14\":\"\",\"68\":[\"321\"],\"29\":\"The online outlet for The Kent Stater and TV2 KSU and the best breaking news source in Kent and Portage County\",\"26\":{\"149\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/kentwired\\/\"}},\"150\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/kentwired\"}},\"151\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/KentWired\\/\"}},\"152\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kentwired.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"\",\"89\":\"https:\\/\\/www.kentwired.com\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:39:20', '2017-07-17 20:39:20', 'ce445909-6d2e-4b63-983f-4d4b9e8c1e68'),
 ('841', '10', '4', '1', 'en_us', '34', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A Magazine\",\"slug\":\"a-magazine\",\"postDate\":1487886960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>A Magazine is Kent State\'s publication for all things fashion, beauty and culture on campus and beyond. A Magazine focuses on women\'s and men\'s fashion providing its audience with the latest fashion industry news and more in print, online and through social media. It is distributed at Kent State and the Fashion School\\u2019s New York studio.&nbsp;A Magazine steps outside just the Kent State campus. From New York City to Florence, Italy and Hong Kong, back to Kent, Ohio, we have students studying and producing content from all over the world<br><\\/p>\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"338\"],\"14\":[\"46\"],\"68\":[\"313\"],\"29\":\"A Magazine is Kent State\\u2019s student-run fashion magazine and is the hub for all things fashion, beauty and culture related\",\"26\":{\"140\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/amagksu\\/\"}},\"141\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/AMagKSU\"}},\"142\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\" http:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/amagksu\\/\"}},\"143\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/theamag.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Fashion. Beauty. Culture. \",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.theamag.com\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:40:32', '2017-07-17 20:40:32', '2f207012-22d1-4dc8-bea7-d152a6ecc8c8'),
 ('842', '14', '4', '1', 'en_us', '20', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"The Burr\",\"slug\":\"the-burr\",\"postDate\":1488208860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\",\"69\"],\"1\":\"<p>The Burr Magazine is Kent State University\\u2019s first student magazine, made by the students for the students. The Burr publishes a semesterly&nbsp;magazine that explores big issues and burning ideas, as well as fascinating people and the consuming preoccupations of its college audience. Each issue contains a compelling mix of how-to articles, original reporting and personal essays. TheBurr.com features Web and multimedia stories, as well as blogs on lifestyle issues, including relationships, fashion and entertainment.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"242\"],\"14\":[\"48\"],\"68\":[\"314\"],\"29\":\"Exploring big issues, burning ideas, fascinating people and preoccupations of its audience\",\"26\":{\"145\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/theburrmagazine\\/\"}},\"146\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/TheBurrMagazine\"}},\"147\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/theburrmagazine\\/\"}},\"148\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/theburr.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Providing award-winning student journalism since 1986\",\"89\":\"https:\\/\\/www.theburr.com\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:40:51', '2017-07-17 20:40:51', '2234c15f-2019-45f6-a31a-055f0c4569ef'),
 ('843', '15', '4', '1', 'en_us', '29', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"The Kent Stater\",\"slug\":\"kent-stater\",\"postDate\":1488208860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>The Kent Stater is an award-winning student-run newspaper. Reaching more than 9,500 people per issue, the Stater keeps the community up-to-date with campus, local and national news, sports and features. The Stater publishes on Monday and Thursday and has a&nbsp;circulation of 6,000 per day. During the summer months, The Kent Stater runs special print issues and a special start of the school year issue. The Kent Stater publishes online with media partner, TV2 KSU, at KentWired.com.<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"244\"],\"14\":[\"51\"],\"68\":[\"327\"],\"29\":\"The independent news team covering KSU and the Kent community \",\"26\":{\"227\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\" https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/kentwired\"}},\"228\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/kentwired\\/\"}},\"229\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/KentWired\\/\"}},\"230\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kentwired.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"The Independent Student Newspaper of Kent State University\",\"89\":\"https:\\/\\/www.kentwired.com\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:41:21', '2017-07-17 20:41:21', 'f6f6dd1c-9a61-4a22-8254-00eb64235017'),
 ('844', '24', '4', '1', 'en_us', '26', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Luna Negra\",\"slug\":\"luna-negra\",\"postDate\":1488484140,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>Luna Negra, though sometimes under different names, has been around since 1956. It began under the English department, where it found its footing within the campus\\u2019s cultural atmosphere. Since then, the publication has been a staple of the university, witnessing the path Kent State has taken through the decades. We have published works describing the culture of collegiate 1950s, the Kent State shootings, and 9\\/11; the literary pieces published by Luna Negra, written by the students themselves, have chronicled every major cultural and historical event of America. Since its inception, and still to today, Luna Negra is run by students and filled with student content. We strive to foster creative activity across campus and seek to be the keeper and encourager of the student body\\u2019s creative spirit.<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"308\"],\"14\":[\"53\"],\"68\":[\"325\"],\"29\":\"Kent State\\u2019s literary and arts journal publishing a blend of poetry, prose, photography and illustration\",\"26\":{\"129\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/lunanegramag\\/\"}},\"130\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/lunanegramagazine\\/\"}},\"131\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/lunanegramag\"}},\"132\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/www.lunanegramag.com\\/\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Kent State\'s Literary and Arts Journal\",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.lunanegramag.com\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:42:05', '2017-07-17 20:42:05', 'ca8d3287-01ff-444d-9efb-6380b377b68c'),
 ('845', '20', '4', '1', 'en_us', '30', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"TV2 KSU\",\"slug\":\"tv2\",\"postDate\":1488483960,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"42\"],\"1\":\"<p>TV2 is Kent State\'s award-winning television station that strives to be Truly Portage County. From local news and sports to entertainment buzz and important social issues surrounding the region, TV2 covers the Kent State and Portage County area like no other television station can, while educating and preparing students for the future. TV2 is found online with media partner The Kent Stater at kentwired.com,&nbsp;reaching more than 26,000 homes on Spectrum Cable channel 16 and more than 7500 KSU students on campus television station 2-2.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"1\",\"13\":[\"309\"],\"14\":[\"55\"],\"68\":[\"319\"],\"29\":\"Award-winning television that strives to be \\\"Truly Portage County\\\" with news, sports and entertainment programming\",\"26\":{\"153\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"instagram\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/tv2ksu\\/\"}},\"154\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"twitter\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/TV2KSU\"}},\"155\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"facebook\",\"address\":\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/tv2ksu\\/\"}},\"222\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kentwired.com\\/tv2\\/\"}}},\"72\":{\"323\":{\"type\":\"link\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"linkName\":\"TV2 Live Stream\",\"linkUrl\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kentwired.com\\/tv2\\/live\\/\"}}},\"21\":\"Truly Portage County \",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kentwired.com\\/tv2\\/\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:42:48', '2017-07-17 20:42:48', '0aa2d1cf-5c42-40dd-a3ba-3e5226b75cbe'),
 ('846', '329', '4', '1', 'en_us', '12', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kent Cribs\",\"slug\":\"kent-cribs\",\"postDate\":1498766820,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"69\"],\"1\":\"<p>The premier apartment finder for Kent, Ohio and Kent State University. &nbsp;If you\'re looking for a place to live, you\'ll find ads with full-color photos, floor plans, videos and direct contact to property owners. If you\'re looking to reach students, staff, faculty and community members, this is your place. We get visitors from all over Ohio and the world looking for the perfect place to call home for four years or more.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"\",\"13\":[\"343\"],\"14\":[\"331\"],\"68\":[\"330\"],\"29\":\"Kent\'s premier apartment-finding website\",\"26\":{\"342\":{\"type\":\"socialMediaBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"socialName\":\"website\",\"address\":\"www.kentcribs.com\"}}},\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"Your apartment search just got easier\",\"89\":\"http:\\/\\/www.kentcribs.com\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:43:19', '2017-07-17 20:43:19', '64834f41-52eb-4e75-989f-13bfa9e9b7bd'),
 ('847', '93', '4', '1', 'en_us', '17', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Transitions\",\"slug\":\"transitions\",\"postDate\":1492115640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"31\":[\"68\"],\"1\":\"<p>Transitions magazine is a go-to guide about area restaurants, shopping, banks, ATMs, hotels, transportation and other tips to make the first year at Kent State successful. It is endorsed by Destination Kent State and is given to students and their parents\\/guardians during the freshman orientation program.<\\/p>\",\"36\":\"\",\"13\":[\"348\"],\"14\":\"\",\"68\":[\"322\"],\"29\":\"Transitions magazine is the new student\'s go-to guide for everything Kent\",\"26\":\"\",\"72\":\"\",\"21\":\"\",\"89\":\"\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:43:43', '2017-07-17 20:43:43', '043ff031-5c5f-4c32-b4dc-3d353bfc77db'),
 ('848', '61', '12', '1', 'en_us', '15', '', '{\"typeId\":\"12\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Advertise with Student Media\",\"slug\":\"advertising\",\"postDate\":1492961215,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>We are your direct access to more than 70,000 people. We connect you to our audience through award-winning digital, print, film and broadcast media.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We have been serving Kent State University and the Kent community for more than 80 years with independent student-produced media. We have the outlets you need to reach the target audience you want.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We look forward to partnering with you and look forward to your success.<\\/p>\",\"13\":[\"303\"],\"67\":[\"268\"],\"21\":\"It starts with you. \"}}', '2017-07-17 20:43:58', '2017-07-17 20:43:58', 'bfb2140b-7700-4aac-8c6b-2068f231938a'),
 ('849', '61', '12', '1', 'en_us', '16', '', '{\"typeId\":\"12\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Advertise with Student Media\",\"slug\":\"advertising\",\"postDate\":1492961215,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>We are your direct access to more than 70,000 people. We connect you to our audience through award-winning digital, print, film and broadcast media.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We have been serving Kent State University and the Kent community for more than 80 years with independent student-produced media. We have the outlets you need to reach the target audience you want.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We look forward to partnering with you and look forward to your success.<\\/p>\",\"13\":[\"303\"],\"67\":[\"268\"],\"21\":\"It starts with you. \"}}', '2017-07-17 20:44:18', '2017-07-17 20:44:18', 'e69ae143-4e47-49d5-8254-43791bd0113a');
INSERT INTO `craft_entryversions` (`id`, `entryId`, `sectionId`, `creatorId`, `locale`, `num`, `notes`, `data`, `dateCreated`, `dateUpdated`, `uid`) VALUES
 ('850', '60', '11', '1', 'en_us', '27', '', '{\"typeId\":\"11\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Get Involved\",\"slug\":\"get-involved\",\"postDate\":1492711027,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Student Media is open to any students, staff or faculty at Kent State. Start as early as your freshman year and get involved in any of dozens of positions across our 10 Student Media partners. Gain important experience that will set you apart from your fellow students. Come share your voice and gain practical experience to help launch your career. To get started, check out current openings below or contact Kevin Dilley, director of Student Media, at kdilley@kent.edu.<\\/p>\",\"51\":{\"231\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How can I become a student media leader?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Leaders of each Student Media partner are selected by the Student Media Board in the fall and spring of each year for the following semester or semesters. To be considered, you must be must have at least a verified cumulative 2.25 Grade Point Average at the time of application and maintain a cumulative 2.25 GPA and be in good standing with the University during your term as leader. &nbsp;To be a compensated student leader, you must be enrolled in a minimum of eight credit hours as an undergraduate student and a minimum of six as a graduate student during their term. You&nbsp;do not need to be majors enrolled in the School of Journalism and Mass Communication. &nbsp;Candidates applying for leadership positions in the JMC-co-curricular units must have related experience to be considered an applicant.<\\/p>\"}},\"261\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I get paid while working for Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Student Media offers hundreds of paid positions each semester across our 10 Student Media partners. Contact us for more information. <\\/p>\"}},\"262\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I study abroad and still be involved in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Student Media supports students who opt for a semester abroad. Sometimes this can fit into a media outlet\'s content plan for that semester. Also, studying abroad will not affect your ability to continue on a path to a leadership position, if you so choose. <\\/p>\"}},\"263\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Who makes the hiring decisions for Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>It depends on the position you are seeking:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>Top leaders for each media partner are selected by the Student Media Board<\\/li><li>Staff members within each media partner are selected by the student leader in consultation with the adviser<\\/li><li>Staff members in the Student Media office are selected by the professional staff. <\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"264\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How many hours can I work?\",\"answer\":\"<p>That depends on your position and the needs of your outlet. You should talk with your student leader and adviser about the specific needs of each position. If you are in a paid position, you cannot work more than 28 hours each week. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"265\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"If I don\'t see a position I like, can I still work in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Probably, let\'s talk. &nbsp;Student Media is growing and changing as rapidly as the professional fields we strive to emulate. So, if a position doesn\'t exist (and it\'s generally within the wheelhouse of media and communications), let\'s talk and figure out how to make it happen.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"282\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I earn academic credit for my work in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Consult with your academic adviser to see if this is allowed through your program. Some schools allow this and others don\'t. &nbsp;Student Media cooperates with the various academic units on campus.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"283\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How long does my employment last once I\'m hired in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Employment length varies from individual to individual and is decided by the the media partner student leader. &nbsp;Most last until the end of the semester, but other arrangements are possible. &nbsp;Please talk with the student leader for the media partner with which you work or for which you are interested in working. Student leaders have the responsibility to remove staff members who are not performing well and\\/or are not following rules and regulations of Student Media. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"284\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Do I have to reapply for a job in Student Media every semester?\",\"answer\":\"<p>This depends on your job and the media parter for which you work. &nbsp;If your work for a media partner where a new editor is elected each semester, you\'ll likely have to reapply. &nbsp;Some partners have student leaders elected for an entire academic year. It\'s possible that this leader will hire positions for the whole year. This is their decision. <\\/p>\"}},\"285\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I work for more than one outlet at the same time during a semester?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. The university limits your paid hours to 28 hours per week in total for all university jobs for which you are paid. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"286\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I volunteer at a Student Media publication?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Some jobs are paid, others are volunteer or on a contributor basis. Check with the student leader for each organization to see what opportunities exist at the moment for that media partner.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"287\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Who has editorial control over content?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Student editors and student managers have sole authority to determine content for the media they lead and in turn take full responsibility for the content decisions made.<\\/p>\"}},\"288\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Where can I listen to Black Squirrel Radio?\",\"answer\":\"<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/blacksquirrelradio.com\\\">http:\\/\\/blacksquirrelradio.com<\\/a><\\/p>\"}},\"289\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"On which channel is TV2 broadcast?\",\"answer\":\"<p>We broadcast on channel 2.2 on Kent State\'s campus, and off-campus on Charter Spectrum channel 16. &nbsp;TV2 also streams live and archives shows at www.kentwired.com\\/tv2.<\\/p>\"}}},\"13\":[\"248\"],\"56\":{\"232\":{\"type\":\"employeeOpportunities\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"hiring\":\"A Magazine\",\"position\":\"Graphic Designer\",\"positionDescription\":\"description\",\"contactInformation\":\"Mary Smith\",\"contactEmail\":\"\"}}},\"21\":\"Start your freshman year. Stay until you graduate. \"}}', '2017-07-17 20:44:47', '2017-07-17 20:44:47', '4fcd1bf9-4bf6-4b0a-bcd1-7bcc7954d63e'),
 ('851', '60', '11', '1', 'en_us', '28', '', '{\"typeId\":\"11\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Get Involved\",\"slug\":\"get-involved\",\"postDate\":1492711027,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Student Media is open to any students, staff or faculty at Kent State. Start as early as your freshman year and get involved in any of dozens of positions across our 10 Student Media partners. Gain important experience that will set you apart from your fellow students. Come share your voice and gain practical experience to help launch your career. To get started, check out current openings below or contact Kevin Dilley, director of Student Media, at kdilley@kent.edu.<\\/p>\",\"51\":{\"231\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How can I become a student media leader?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Leaders of each Student Media partner are selected by the Student Media Board in the fall and spring of each year for the following semester or semesters. To be considered, you must be must have at least a verified cumulative 2.25 Grade Point Average at the time of application and maintain a cumulative 2.25 GPA and be in good standing with the University during your term as leader. &nbsp;To be a compensated student leader, you must be enrolled in a minimum of eight credit hours as an undergraduate student and a minimum of six as a graduate student during their term. You&nbsp;do not need to be majors enrolled in the School of Journalism and Mass Communication. &nbsp;Candidates applying for leadership positions in the JMC-co-curricular units must have related experience to be considered an applicant.<\\/p>\"}},\"261\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I get paid while working for Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Student Media offers hundreds of paid positions each semester across our 10 Student Media partners. Contact us for more information. <\\/p>\"}},\"262\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I study abroad and still be involved in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Student Media supports students who opt for a semester abroad. Sometimes this can fit into a media outlet\'s content plan for that semester. Also, studying abroad will not affect your ability to continue on a path to a leadership position, if you so choose. <\\/p>\"}},\"263\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Who makes the hiring decisions for Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>It depends on the position you are seeking:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>Top leaders for each media partner are selected by the Student Media Board<\\/li><li>Staff members within each media partner are selected by the student leader in consultation with the adviser<\\/li><li>Staff members in the Student Media office are selected by the professional staff. <\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"264\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How many hours can I work?\",\"answer\":\"<p>That depends on your position and the needs of your outlet. You should talk with your student leader and adviser about the specific needs of each position. If you are in a paid position, you cannot work more than 28 hours each week. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"265\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"If I don\'t see a position I like, can I still work in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Probably, let\'s talk. &nbsp;Student Media is growing and changing as rapidly as the professional fields we strive to emulate. So, if a position doesn\'t exist (and it\'s generally within the wheelhouse of media and communications), let\'s talk and figure out how to make it happen.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"282\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I earn academic credit for my work in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Consult with your academic adviser to see if this is allowed through your program. Some schools allow this and others don\'t. &nbsp;Student Media cooperates with the various academic units on campus.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"283\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How long does my employment last once I\'m hired in Student Media?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Employment length varies from individual to individual and is decided by the the media partner student leader. &nbsp;Most last until the end of the semester, but other arrangements are possible. &nbsp;Please talk with the student leader for the media partner with which you work or for which you are interested in working. Student leaders have the responsibility to remove staff members who are not performing well and\\/or are not following rules and regulations of Student Media. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"284\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Do I have to reapply for a job in Student Media every semester?\",\"answer\":\"<p>This depends on your job and the media parter for which you work. &nbsp;If your work for a media partner where a new editor is elected each semester, you\'ll likely have to reapply. &nbsp;Some partners have student leaders elected for an entire academic year. It\'s possible that this leader will hire positions for the whole year. This is their decision. <\\/p>\"}},\"285\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I work for more than one outlet at the same time during a semester?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. The university limits your paid hours to 28 hours per week in total for all university jobs for which you are paid. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"286\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Can I volunteer at a Student Media publication?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes. Some jobs are paid, others are volunteer or on a contributor basis. Check with the student leader for each organization to see what opportunities exist at the moment for that media partner.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"287\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Who has editorial control over content?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Student editors and student managers have sole authority to determine content for the media they lead and in turn take full responsibility for the content decisions made.<\\/p>\"}},\"288\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"Where can I listen to Black Squirrel Radio?\",\"answer\":\"<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/blacksquirrelradio.com\\\">http:\\/\\/blacksquirrelradio.com<\\/a><\\/p>\"}},\"289\":{\"type\":\"faqs\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"On which channel is TV2 broadcast?\",\"answer\":\"<p>We broadcast on channel 2.2 on Kent State\'s campus, and off-campus on Charter Spectrum channel 16. &nbsp;TV2 also streams live and archives shows at www.kentwired.com\\/tv2.<\\/p>\"}}},\"13\":[\"248\"],\"56\":{\"232\":{\"type\":\"employeeOpportunities\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"hiring\":\"A Magazine\",\"position\":\"Graphic Designer\",\"positionDescription\":\"description\",\"contactInformation\":\"Mary Smith\",\"contactEmail\":\"\"}}},\"21\":\"Start your freshman year. Stay until you graduate. \"}}', '2017-07-17 20:44:47', '2017-07-17 20:44:47', '85ec6a3a-f32f-41c5-bc72-e274e4eb996f'),
 ('852', '62', '13', '1', 'en_us', '21', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Contact Student Media\",\"slug\":\"contact\",\"postDate\":1489688145,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>We\'d love to hear from you, whether it\'s about getting involved with Student Media, reaching out about individual partners and their content, or for advertising opportunities.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>For advertising contact us at <a href=\\\"mailto:ads@ksustudentmedia.com\\\">ads@ksustudentmedia.com<\\/a>, 330-672-6306, or drop by our office during business hours, Monday through Friday 8 a.m to 5 p.m. in 205 Franklin Hall on the Kent State University Kent campus.&nbsp;<\\/li><li>For general Student Media questions, reach out to Director of Student Media, Kevin Dilley, at <a href=\\\"mailto:kdilley@kent.edu\\\">kdilley@kent.edu<\\/a>  or 330-672-0887. You\'ll also find him in 205 Franklin Hall.&nbsp;<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"13\":[\"271\"],\"21\":\"How can we help?\"}}', '2017-07-17 20:45:16', '2017-07-17 20:45:16', 'e7077065-2c00-4691-8cf5-99c6462cf6b9'),
