 ('863', '58', '9', '1', 'en_us', '43', '', '{\"typeId\":\"9\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"About us\",\"slug\":\"about\",\"postDate\":1492560894,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"103\":\"<p>Paragraph description of awards can go here.<\\/p>\",\"1\":\"<p><strong>For more than 90 years,<\\/strong> students at Kent State University have been finding ways to tell stories and disseminate vital and compelling information.\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Even before formal journalism education classes had been established, students were chasing leads and documenting the events shaping our history, sharing their work in the Normal High School News and The Chestnut Burr in 1914, The Kentonian in 1915 and eventually the first issue of The Kent Stater on July 29, 1926.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>We now are more than 700 students<\\/strong> working with 10 distinct and independent Student Media partners who create unique content distributed across 34 different outlets on multiple platforms. Our students are supported in their efforts by a strong fabric of faculty advisers, professional staff, university support and, of course, financial support from the students of Kent State University.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>And while the methods have varied since those early publications, our core philosophy has remained constant: empower students to create valued sources and encourage excellence.\\r\\n  <\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Won\\u2019t you join us and continue the story?<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"11\":[\"166\"],\"13\":[\"246\"],\"100\":{\"seoMainEntityCategory\":\"CreativeWork\",\"seoMainEntityOfPage\":\"WebPage\",\"seoTitleSource\":\"field\",\"seoTitleSourceField\":\"title\",\"seoTitleUnparsed\":\"\",\"seoDescriptionSource\":\"custom\",\"seoDescriptionSourceField\":\"title\",\"seoDescriptionUnparsed\":\"\",\"seoKeywordsSource\":\"custom\",\"seoKeywordsSourceField\":\"title\",\"seoKeywordsUnparsed\":\"\",\"seoImageIdSource\":\"custom\",\"seoImageIdSourceField\":\"heroImage\",\"